                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d719">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/8994: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Valencia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wallner</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Valencia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-02-26T20:00:00-04:30"
                            >February 26, 1939—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 27—7:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>19. During the last week conditions in the Republic have evolved somewhat towards
                    the end which all now admit to be inevitable and believe will be precipitated by
                    France’s and England’s recognition of Franco. Passports are being issued to
                    leading politicians and government officials. The apparent intention to leave
                    the lesser lights behind gives rise to fears of a last minute outbreak led by
                    the Communists, though public order is still excellent.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wallner</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
